A man who was seriously injured in a car crash, has been robbed by unscrupulous bystanders while waiting for medical assistance. ADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads

Rescue Care’s Ceron Meadows said the man sustained serious injuries after his vehicle hit a pole on Cato Manor Road on Wednesday afternoon. “The driver who had serious injuries as a result of the collision was then approached by bystanders who he thought were coming to assist him however they robbed him of all his valuables,” said Meadows. 

When paramedics arrived at the scene, they found the badly damaged vehicle on the roadside. The man was stabilised by paramedics on the scene before being transported to a nearby hospital for further care. 

In a separate crash, 12 children were injured after their school taxi swerved off Dambuza Road in Marianhill on Wednesday morning.

 

Rescue Care paramedics arrived on the scene just after 7am to find the taxi down an embankment. Twelve children all under the age of 11 had sustained minor injuries. More ambulances were dispatched to assist and once all the injured were stabilised on the scene, they were transported to various Durban Hospitals for the further care. 

 

Police were on both scenes an the causes of the crashes are being investigated.
The Mercury